# Backend build-context ignore file (build context is ./server — the root
# .dockerignore does NOT apply here; each docker build context reads only its
# own .dockerignore).
#
# Two goals:
#   1. SECRETS never enter image layers. Credentials are provided at runtime:
#      google-tts-credentials.json is bind-mounted by docker-compose.prod.yml,
#      and env comes from env_file/environment entries — never from baked .env.
#   2. Keep the context small: host node_modules (musl/glibc mismatch risk),
#      dist, logs, and the TTS disk cache are all rebuilt or mounted at runtime.

# Secrets — runtime-mounted, never baked
google-tts-credentials.json
*credentials*.json
.env
.env.*

# Host artifacts rebuilt inside the image
node_modules
dist

# Runtime state (bind-mounted in prod; regenerated in dev)
logs
cache

# Non-runtime files
tests
*.test.ts
*.test.js
README.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
auth-setup-guide.md
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
